id: pm-ablm
title: "GH-265: schema unknown subcommands must not create custom types"
description: "GitHub #265 reports pm schema <unknown-token> (for example list-statuses/help/show-all) is routed through add-type shorthand and silently mutates schema/types.json. Duplicate check: pm search for schema unknown subcommand/list-statuses/help/show-all found closed historical schema work but no open item for this bug. Fix should preserve explicit add-type while rejecting read-subcommand typos with allowed guidance."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-17T22:59:33.033Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-17T23:12:42.387Z"
author: codex-audit-agent
parent: pm-8jdc
resolution: Fixed GH #265 by preventing read-like unknown schema tokens from entering shorthand add-type.
expected_result: pm schema list-statuses/help/show-all/list-types/types should exit usage and leave schema/types.json unchanged; explicit pm schema add-type remains available.
actual_result: Schema shorthand now rejects reserved schema verb/read-like tokens; unit/temp-tracker regression/manual SHA reproduction/full coverage passed.
